from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    i = 0   # --- py stmt 3
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 4
    chars = set()   # --- py stmt 5
    for j, c in enumerate(s):   # --- py stmt 6
        if c == ' ':   # --- py stmt 7
            continue   # --- py stmt 8
        elif c == '*':   # --- py stmt 9
            break   # --- py stmt 10
        while c in chars:   # --- py stmt 11
            chars.remove(s[i])   # --- py stmt 12
            i += 1   # --- py stmt 13
        chars.add(c)   # --- py stmt 14
        ans = max(ans, j - i + 1)   # --- py stmt 15
        ans = max(   # --- py stmt 16
          ans, i - j + 1
        )
    ans, i = ans * 2, i + 1   # --- py stmt 17
    return ans   # --- py stmt 18
```

from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(text: str, brokenLetters: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    letters = set(brokenLetters)   # --- py stmt 3
    res = 0   # --- py stmt 4
    for word in text.split():   # --- py stmt 5
        find = False   # --- py stmt 6
        for letter in letters:   # --- py stmt 7
            if letter in word:   # --- py stmt 8
                find = True   # --- py stmt 9
                break   # --- py stmt 10
        if not find:   # --- py stmt 11
            res += 1   # --- py stmt 12
    return res   # --- py stmt 13
```

function f_gold(text, brokenLetters) {   // --- py stmt 2
    var letters = new Set(brokenLetters);   // --- py stmt 3
    var res = 0;   // --- py stmt 4
    for (var word of text.split(/\s+/)) {   // --- py stmt 5
        var find = false;   // --- py stmt 6
        for (var letter of letters) {   // --- py stmt 7
            if (word.includes(letter)) {   // --- py stmt 8
                find = true;   // --- py stmt 9
                break;   // --- py stmt 10
            }
        }
        if (!find) {   // --- py stmt 11
            res += 1;   // --- py stmt 12
        }
    }
    return res;   // --- py stmt 13
}
